1
00:00:00,570 --> 00:00:01,710
Hello.

2
00:00:02,070 --> 00:00:03,170
Hello there.

3
00:00:03,810 --> 00:00:04,910
Is that CEO Chae's daughter?

4
00:00:05,510 --> 00:00:07,010
Right, Seong Hye.

5
00:00:07,010 --> 00:00:09,410
Say hello. This is your great-aunt.

6
00:00:11,580 --> 00:00:13,420
Hello, it's nice to meet you.

7
00:00:13,690 --> 00:00:15,820
Yes, of course.
Goodness, you are a pretty one.

8
00:00:15,820 --> 00:00:16,990
Let's sit down.

9
00:00:18,190 --> 00:00:22,460
She insisted on making soybean paste stew
for you, Grandfather.

10
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:25,400
I see.

11
00:00:25,900 --> 00:00:28,470
Suk Hee makes a tasty soybean paste stew.

12
00:00:28,470 --> 00:00:29,870
It'll just be a minute.

13
00:00:36,740 --> 00:00:37,840
You've got to be kidding me.

14
00:00:38,310 --> 00:00:41,510
What if that's the necklace
Father said he gave her?

15
00:00:42,410 --> 00:00:44,620
I can't let Father see that,
no matter what.

16
00:00:49,790 --> 00:00:50,790
Careful.

17
00:01:09,040 --> 00:01:12,140
- Oh my gosh!
- Goodness!

18
00:01:12,340 --> 00:01:14,550
- Mom!
- What a mess.

19
00:01:14,550 --> 00:01:16,680
What do you think you're doing?

20
00:01:17,320 --> 00:01:18,920
Seong Hye, are you okay? Did it burn you?

21
00:01:18,920 --> 00:01:20,150
No, I'm fine.

22
00:01:20,620 --> 00:01:21,790
It's no big deal.

23
00:01:21,990 --> 00:01:24,990
Don't just stand there!
Go and get a towel.

24
00:01:25,060 --> 00:01:26,060
Yes, dear.

25
00:01:26,060 --> 00:01:27,760
Mom, are you okay? Did you burn yourself?

26
00:01:28,290 --> 00:01:30,330
Are you all right, Auntie?

27
00:01:31,060 --> 00:01:32,260
Your clothes are completely ruined.

28
00:01:32,830 --> 00:01:35,800
- I'm sure it will smell awful.
- I didn't do it!

29
00:01:41,540 --> 00:01:43,980
That's a habit my sister had.

30
00:01:46,810 --> 00:01:50,050
Jang Mi. Take her home.

31
00:01:50,220 --> 00:01:53,320
What is all this during dinner?
We can't even eat in peace.

32
00:01:53,450 --> 00:01:54,750
I'm sorry, Grandfather.

33
00:01:54,820 --> 00:01:56,250
You should have been more careful.

34
00:01:56,250 --> 00:01:58,320
How could this happen with our aunt here?

35
00:01:59,060 --> 00:02:00,290
Are you okay, Auntie?

36
00:02:01,430 --> 00:02:02,990
I'm sorry, Grandfather.

37
00:02:03,860 --> 00:02:05,730
I didn't do it.

38
00:02:06,430 --> 00:02:10,440
All right, that's enough. Just go. Okay?

39
00:02:11,570 --> 00:02:13,740
I'm sorry, everyone. Mom, come on.

40
00:02:25,780 --> 00:02:29,520
Auntie, you must have been
very startled during dinner.

41
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:32,790
But still, it's a huge relief
you weren't burned.

42
00:02:33,220 --> 00:02:35,030
Mistakes happen.

43
00:02:35,660 --> 00:02:36,660
But, Auntie...

44
00:02:37,460 --> 00:02:41,030
If you don't mind my asking, there was
something I've been wondering about.

45
00:02:41,570 --> 00:02:43,670
- What is it?
- It's about Dong Seok.

46
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:47,510
Why wasn't he in that photo from earlier?

47
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:50,640
In the family photo
from your niece's 100th-day celebration,

48
00:02:50,880 --> 00:02:52,440
Dong Seok was nowhere to be seen.

49
00:02:53,910 --> 00:02:56,880
I'm not really sure.

50
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:59,950
According to what you said,

51
00:03:00,180 --> 00:03:02,850
it was a cherished family photo
taken at the time...

52
00:03:02,890 --> 00:03:04,590
while Father was on the run
after his bankruptcy.

53
00:03:05,290 --> 00:03:07,830
And yet, the fact that
Dong Seok is missing...

54
00:03:08,130 --> 00:03:09,630
is something I just can't
wrap my head around.

55
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:17,740
Was Dong Seok adopted by any chance?

56
00:03:19,170 --> 00:03:21,210
I have no idea.

57
00:03:21,770 --> 00:03:24,840
I left right after Eun Hye died, so...

58
00:03:24,910 --> 00:03:28,450
So you're saying Dong Seok
hadn't been adopted yet.

59
00:03:29,480 --> 00:03:32,050
But Dong Seok was supposed to be around
before Eun Hye died.

60
00:03:34,390 --> 00:03:35,850
Don't you worry, Auntie.

61
00:03:36,190 --> 00:03:37,990
I'll pretend I don't know a thing.

62
00:03:38,790 --> 00:03:41,560
I don't want to needlessly worry Father.

63
00:03:42,530 --> 00:03:46,530
He's already suffered his whole life
because of what happened to Eun Hye.

64
00:03:49,300 --> 00:03:52,900
Well, since it's all come to light...

65
00:03:53,610 --> 00:03:56,670
I left right after it happened,
so I don't know for sure.

66
00:03:57,310 --> 00:03:58,940
But from what I heard,

67
00:03:59,580 --> 00:04:02,780
after losing my sister
and his daughter like that,

68
00:04:03,180 --> 00:04:06,080
my brother-in-law adopted Dong Seok.

69
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:09,350
So that's what it was.

70
00:04:09,590 --> 00:04:13,020
They said he cherished Dong Seok
as if he were his own son.

71
00:04:13,690 --> 00:04:16,330
He wasn't even his own flesh and blood,

72
00:04:16,460 --> 00:04:18,800
but he wanted to leave him
his entire fortune.

73
00:04:19,130 --> 00:04:20,200
Of course.

74
00:04:21,830 --> 00:04:26,570
After all, he accepted my daughter
and me as his real family.

75
00:04:26,770 --> 00:04:28,410
Even if he finds Eun Hye,

76
00:04:28,540 --> 00:04:32,410
he would never turn his back
on you and your daughter.

77
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:35,680
Of course. We're already a family.

78
00:04:36,650 --> 00:04:37,920
What does this mean then?

79
00:04:38,020 --> 00:04:40,250
This means I can't use the fact
that Dong Seok and Jung Suk Hee...

80
00:04:40,250 --> 00:04:41,620
are siblings to my advantage.

81
00:04:42,790 --> 00:04:43,790
Now that it's come to this,

82
00:04:44,420 --> 00:04:47,460
Jung Suk Hee will soon be recognized
as Chairman Ma's daughter.

83
00:04:47,730 --> 00:04:48,930
What am I going to do?

84
00:05:05,310 --> 00:05:08,150
I think I'd better call my brother-in-law.

85
00:05:08,310 --> 00:05:09,880
What do you mean, Auntie?

86
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:13,690
I'm talking about that woman from earlier.

87
00:05:14,290 --> 00:05:18,460
Her looks and her mannerisms
were so much like my sister's.

88
00:05:18,520 --> 00:05:19,520
What?

89
00:05:19,790 --> 00:05:22,160
What on earth are you talking about?

90
00:05:22,290 --> 00:05:24,300
Whenever my sister got flustered,

91
00:05:24,530 --> 00:05:27,700
she'd grab both of her earlobes
like this...

92
00:05:27,770 --> 00:05:30,230
and hold them to cool down.
It was a habit of hers.

93
00:05:30,300 --> 00:05:32,400
But isn't that a common habit?

94
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:35,370
I do it all the time.

95
00:05:35,370 --> 00:05:37,180
But in that moment,

96
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:40,210
it was like my sister
had come back to life.

97
00:05:40,910 --> 00:05:43,680
No matter how I look at it,
this is no mere coincidence.

98
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:48,250
Auntie, I know you were shocked,

99
00:05:48,690 --> 00:05:50,890
but you can't let Father
hear a word of it.

100
00:05:50,890 --> 00:05:52,060
What? Why not?

101
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:55,860
- Why can't my brother-in-law know?
- Father can't stand her.

102
00:05:56,490 --> 00:05:58,300
She's nothing but trouble.

103
00:05:59,260 --> 00:06:00,260
That may be, but...

104
00:06:00,330 --> 00:06:02,300
I'm already worried
about his high blood pressure.

105
00:06:03,570 --> 00:06:07,070
Imagine telling him
that some simple-minded stranger...

106
00:06:07,710 --> 00:06:10,440
has the same habit as his late wife.

107
00:06:11,310 --> 00:06:14,510
Father would be so devastated,
he'd collapse on the spot.

108
00:06:14,580 --> 00:06:17,820
Is his health really that bad?

109
00:06:17,820 --> 00:06:18,820
Yes.

110
00:06:19,450 --> 00:06:22,190
I'm on pins and needles
whenever I see him these days.

111
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:24,960
A woman showed up once before,
claiming to be his daughter,

112
00:06:25,160 --> 00:06:27,960
and Father nearly collapsed
from the shock.

113
00:06:28,990 --> 00:06:30,260
I had no idea.

114
00:06:32,530 --> 00:06:33,630
In that case.

115
00:06:37,370 --> 00:06:41,040
Mom, it's not a big deal.
Don't worry, okay?

116
00:06:42,210 --> 00:06:46,140
Chae Hwa Young pushed Suk Hee like this.

117
00:06:46,210 --> 00:06:48,280
What? Chae Hwa Young did this?

118
00:06:48,880 --> 00:06:52,180
Then why didn't you say anything?
It wasn't your fault then.

119
00:06:52,280 --> 00:06:56,750
Suk Hee was scared.
Suk Hee made another mess.

120
00:07:00,060 --> 00:07:01,260
Mom, just a second.

121
00:07:13,140 --> 00:07:15,940
How could she be Ma Eun Hye?

122
00:07:16,470 --> 00:07:18,140
Chairman Ma can never find out about this.

123
00:07:19,710 --> 00:07:22,210
What? It's the thief!

124
00:07:22,210 --> 00:07:24,250
Chae Hwa Young is a thief!

125
00:07:25,050 --> 00:07:26,050
Goodness!

126
00:07:27,150 --> 00:07:29,650
Who do you think you're hitting?
Hey, Jung Suk Hee!

127
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:31,220
You're a thief! Evil Chae Hwa Young!

128
00:07:31,220 --> 00:07:32,360
Why you...

129
00:07:32,420 --> 00:07:34,890
Hey! Let go of me!

130
00:07:35,790 --> 00:07:36,790
- I said, let go!
- You want to mess with me?

131
00:07:37,960 --> 00:07:39,300
What do you think you're doing?

132
00:07:40,260 --> 00:07:41,930
Lawyer Kang, you don't
even know what happened.

133
00:07:41,930 --> 00:07:43,500
She hit me first!

134
00:07:43,570 --> 00:07:47,870
She's a bad person.
Chae Hwa Young pushed me,

135
00:07:48,070 --> 00:07:50,640
and I spilled the stew. She's a thief!

136
00:07:51,540 --> 00:07:54,180
Chae Hwa Young, why are you here again?

137
00:07:54,180 --> 00:07:55,210
What more could you want?

138
00:07:55,380 --> 00:07:57,880
You did this just to make my mom look bad
in front of Grandfather, didn't you?

139
00:07:57,950 --> 00:08:00,950
Why do you hate Jang Mi
and her mother so much?

140
00:08:01,250 --> 00:08:02,690
It's because of Jung Suk Hee.

141
00:08:02,820 --> 00:08:05,620
My baby died because of you!
My baby is dead!

142
00:08:06,390 --> 00:08:07,890
You're the murderer, Jung Suk Hee!

143
00:08:08,260 --> 00:08:11,100
And Oh Jang Mi, that makes you
a murderer's daughter. Got it?

144
00:08:13,870 --> 00:08:15,100
Don't you ever come back here!

145
00:08:15,770 --> 00:08:17,900
What was that? Hey, Oh Tae Pyung!

146
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:20,440
How dare you gang up on me?

147
00:08:20,540 --> 00:08:24,540
- Get out. I said, get out!
- You people are unbelievable!

148
00:08:25,380 --> 00:08:27,250
- Get out!
- Unbelievable!

149
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:30,850
I swear, I can't take this anymore!

150
00:08:38,120 --> 00:08:41,060
This is Jung Suk Hee's sample.
Keep it somewhere safe.

151
00:08:41,990 --> 00:08:44,430
I think we need to have a Plan B ready.

152
00:08:45,100 --> 00:08:46,600
We might have to use it again someday.

153
00:08:46,900 --> 00:08:48,600
What's the deal with Ma Dong Seok?

154
00:08:48,870 --> 00:08:50,100
He was adopted.

155
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:53,700
He's not blood-related
to Chairman Ma at all.

156
00:08:53,870 --> 00:08:57,110
Then what about the DNA test we ran
on Seo Rin and Chairman Ma?

157
00:08:57,680 --> 00:08:59,780
How could we have claimed
she was his flesh and blood?

158
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:02,610
That was only possible because
Jung Suk Hee is his blood relative.

159
00:09:02,950 --> 00:09:05,680
Then if Chairman Ma actually does
a DNA test with Seo Rin,

160
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:08,450
wouldn't he just find out that
Jung Suk Hee is his daughter?

161
00:09:08,990 --> 00:09:11,920
- Isn't that strange?
- That sly old fox...

162
00:09:12,160 --> 00:09:15,660
put on a show for us,
acting as if he'd run a DNA test,

163
00:09:16,060 --> 00:09:17,530
but he must've used
Ma Dong Seok's belongings...

164
00:09:18,330 --> 00:09:20,730
to compare with Seo Rin's DNA.

165
00:09:21,170 --> 00:09:23,670
Anyway, it is only a matter of time...

166
00:09:23,970 --> 00:09:26,870
before it comes to light that
Jung Suk Hee is his biological daughter.

167
00:09:27,740 --> 00:09:30,540
We have to make a move first
before that happens.

168
00:09:32,380 --> 00:09:35,280
How did that impostor, Park Young Mi,

169
00:09:36,250 --> 00:09:38,980
know about the necklace
and just show up on her own?

170
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:40,450
I'm terribly sorry, Chairman.

171
00:09:41,450 --> 00:09:44,460
I was so desperate to believe
I had found Miss Eun Hye...

172
00:09:46,020 --> 00:09:47,660
that when I first met the woman,

173
00:09:48,590 --> 00:09:52,100
I first asked her if she had a necklace
from her childhood.

174
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:54,530
But right then and there,

175
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:57,200
she asked,
"You mean the half-heart necklace?"

176
00:09:57,940 --> 00:09:59,200
As soon as I heard her say that,

177
00:09:59,870 --> 00:10:02,240
I was convinced that she was Miss Eun Hye.

178
00:10:02,710 --> 00:10:03,710
Then that means...

179
00:10:04,740 --> 00:10:06,340
that impostor must have,
at the very least,

180
00:10:06,810 --> 00:10:11,180
seen the half-heart necklace in person.

181
00:10:11,750 --> 00:10:14,820
Either that, or she knows a great deal
about our Eun Hye.

182
00:10:15,120 --> 00:10:16,390
Now that you mention it, you're right.

183
00:10:17,360 --> 00:10:19,890
Is that impostor's name
really Park Young Mi?

184
00:10:20,220 --> 00:10:21,830
She's not impersonating a Park Young Mi,
is she?

185
00:10:22,090 --> 00:10:23,090
I think...

186
00:10:23,630 --> 00:10:25,200
that's her actual name.

187
00:10:26,230 --> 00:10:27,260
Go right now...

188
00:10:28,030 --> 00:10:31,100
and dig up every last thing you can
on that impostor!

189
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:36,040
What? You want to register Mom's DNA
with the police?

190
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:38,210
Yes. What have we got to lose?

191
00:10:38,580 --> 00:10:39,580
That's true.

192
00:10:40,180 --> 00:10:41,450
Mom's parents...

193
00:10:42,310 --> 00:10:44,580
I mean, my grandma and grandpa,

194
00:10:44,720 --> 00:10:48,690
could be out there somewhere
desperately searching for her.

195
00:10:48,990 --> 00:10:51,460
That's a good point.
Why didn't I think of that?

196
00:10:51,690 --> 00:10:52,720
But then again,

197
00:10:53,360 --> 00:10:55,490
it's been decades since she was abandoned.

198
00:10:55,490 --> 00:10:59,000
If we register her in the database now,
I'm not sure we'll actually get a match.

199
00:11:00,130 --> 00:11:02,600
Plus, she barely has any memories
from back then.

200
00:11:03,100 --> 00:11:06,500
The fact that she doesn't remember
is exactly why we should rely on science.

201
00:11:06,640 --> 00:11:09,240
Exactly. If her family members...

202
00:11:09,370 --> 00:11:12,340
have already registered their DNA
with the missing persons unit,

203
00:11:12,680 --> 00:11:15,850
the system will flag a match
the second her data is uploaded.

204
00:11:15,910 --> 00:11:17,050
You're right, Baek Ho.

205
00:11:17,380 --> 00:11:20,020
I'm taking Mom to the police station
first thing tomorrow.

206
00:11:20,250 --> 00:11:22,890
Don't get your hopes up too high
if there's no match, Jang Mi.

207
00:11:23,150 --> 00:11:24,520
Don't worry.

208
00:11:25,790 --> 00:11:27,290
Her parents...

209
00:11:27,590 --> 00:11:31,560
might've passed away a long time ago,
given their age.

210
00:11:34,930 --> 00:11:36,130
I really hope you get to meet them.

211
00:11:38,570 --> 00:11:39,570
Yes.

212
00:11:46,580 --> 00:11:48,550
There's no need to be so anxious.

213
00:11:48,550 --> 00:11:50,550
Kang Hyuk, what are we going to do?

214
00:11:51,050 --> 00:11:52,120
What are we going to do?

215
00:11:52,780 --> 00:11:56,050
Jung Suk Hee is undeniably
Chairman Ma's biological daughter.

216
00:11:56,790 --> 00:12:01,090
The day that all comes out,
it's over for me, and for our Jun Ho too.

217
00:12:04,230 --> 00:12:05,230
Hwa Young.

218
00:12:07,430 --> 00:12:09,570
- Let's run away.
- What?

219
00:12:10,030 --> 00:12:11,500
You, me, and Jun Ho.

220
00:12:11,840 --> 00:12:14,170
We can take all the money we've saved
and go abroad.

221
00:12:15,170 --> 00:12:18,680
We could be so much happier
than we are here.

222
00:12:18,740 --> 00:12:20,310
We've got money. What's stopping us?

223
00:12:20,850 --> 00:12:23,680
Leave everything behind
to run off and hide like rats?

224
00:12:24,180 --> 00:12:25,220
Are you crazy?

225
00:12:25,550 --> 00:12:27,250
Why should we be the ones to hide?

226
00:12:27,790 --> 00:12:31,120
Who do you think worked so hard
to make Dream what it is today?

227
00:12:31,190 --> 00:12:32,260
Then what's the alternative?

228
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:35,460
Do you really think
Chairman Ma will never find Jung Suk Hee?

229
00:12:36,060 --> 00:12:37,330
And when he does,

230
00:12:38,160 --> 00:12:40,230
do you think he'll forgive you
for taking Seo Rin...

231
00:12:40,230 --> 00:12:42,270
and destroying Jung Suk Hee?

232
00:12:42,330 --> 00:12:43,670
Do you really think
he'll let you get away with it?

233
00:12:43,970 --> 00:12:46,670
And there's what you did to Oh Bok Gil.

234
00:12:46,670 --> 00:12:48,770
Stop it! Please, just stop!

235
00:12:53,910 --> 00:12:55,080
I love you, Hwa Young.

236
00:12:56,210 --> 00:12:57,880
Jun Ho is my son.

237
00:12:58,220 --> 00:12:59,280
I want to live...

238
00:13:00,180 --> 00:13:02,590
with you, the woman I love,
and Jun Ho, my son.

239
00:13:03,620 --> 00:13:07,530
I want to stop sneaking around
and just live like a real family.

240
00:13:08,990 --> 00:13:10,960
Let's run away together, Hwa Young. Okay?

241
00:13:12,360 --> 00:13:14,670
Please, stop talking such utter nonsense.

242
00:13:14,930 --> 00:13:16,230
Who are you calling your son?

243
00:13:16,970 --> 00:13:18,800
Don't you dare say that nonsense
to me again.

244
00:13:21,340 --> 00:13:22,870
Why can't it be me?

245
00:13:23,140 --> 00:13:24,210
Why?

246
00:13:24,540 --> 00:13:27,040
A pathetic weakling
like Kang Nam Bong is fine,

247
00:13:27,480 --> 00:13:28,680
but why...

248
00:13:30,550 --> 00:13:33,250
am I not good enough when I spent
my whole life living in your shadows?

249
00:13:34,080 --> 00:13:35,690
Do you really have to ask?

250
00:13:38,490 --> 00:13:39,660
Yes, I do.

251
00:13:40,490 --> 00:13:42,090
Tell me clearly why.

252
00:13:43,260 --> 00:13:46,160
- Why Kang Nam Bong?
- Professor Kang is refined.

253
00:13:47,060 --> 00:13:48,900
He's elegant,
as an educated man should be,

254
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:50,530
and he's full of grace.

255
00:13:51,840 --> 00:13:54,440
At least he's not vulgar
and ignorant like you.

256
00:13:57,140 --> 00:13:58,780
And for the record,
Jun Ho is not your son.

257
00:13:59,310 --> 00:14:00,480
Get that through your head.

258
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:04,480
Fine.

259
00:14:07,250 --> 00:14:09,790
I've already done a DNA test,
and I know he's my son.

260
00:14:13,260 --> 00:14:14,960
But if you say he isn't, I guess he isn't.

261
00:14:37,920 --> 00:14:39,180
This is good.

262
00:14:40,380 --> 00:14:41,420
Come in.

263
00:14:42,020 --> 00:14:43,020
Come on in.

264
00:14:45,660 --> 00:14:48,890
Manager Lee. What are you doing here?

265
00:14:49,030 --> 00:14:50,890
This is how we live.

266
00:14:51,660 --> 00:14:54,100
I asked why you're here in our home.

267
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:56,900
He's my guest. Stay out of it.

268
00:14:57,500 --> 00:14:58,640
Your guest?

269
00:14:59,970 --> 00:15:02,410
Please, make yourself comfortable,
Kang Hyuk.

270
00:15:03,270 --> 00:15:04,280
Just a moment.

271
00:15:05,640 --> 00:15:06,740
Wait, what?

272
00:15:07,610 --> 00:15:08,710
"Kang Hyuk?"

273
00:15:12,150 --> 00:15:13,420
Your ramyeon's getting soggy.

274
00:15:14,150 --> 00:15:15,490
Don't mind me. Just eat.

275
00:15:19,390 --> 00:15:20,960
I asked you a question.

276
00:15:21,330 --> 00:15:25,030
What business could you possibly have
with my wife, Han Young Ja, coming here?

277
00:15:25,300 --> 00:15:27,300
Do I have to answer to you?

278
00:15:28,030 --> 00:15:30,430
Please. You're a pathetic nobody.

279
00:15:30,430 --> 00:15:31,470
What did you say?

280
00:15:32,700 --> 00:15:33,970
Goodness.

281
00:15:36,540 --> 00:15:39,780
Look at him.
In his sweats, eating ramyeon.

282
00:15:40,880 --> 00:15:44,750
What could Hwa Young possibly see
in that pathetic excuse for a man?

283
00:15:45,750 --> 00:15:48,920
- What are you looking at?
- Don't get on my nerves.

284
00:15:49,920 --> 00:15:51,320
You wouldn't even last one punch.

285
00:15:51,520 --> 00:15:53,590
What did you say?
You've really crossed the line.

286
00:15:53,590 --> 00:15:54,830
Do you have anything else to say?

287
00:15:59,230 --> 00:16:00,730
What do you think you're doing?

288
00:16:01,230 --> 00:16:02,670
Why are you treating
Manager Lee like this?

289
00:16:03,170 --> 00:16:04,200
Is this it?

290
00:16:04,970 --> 00:16:05,970
Yes.

291
00:16:06,370 --> 00:16:09,440
I'm sorry.
I was supposed to take this to Jun Ho.

292
00:16:10,240 --> 00:16:13,210
Luckily, I ran into you,
and you even gave me a ride.

293
00:16:13,780 --> 00:16:16,810
Thanks for dropping me off, Kang Hyuk.

294
00:16:16,810 --> 00:16:18,020
Don't mention it.

295
00:16:19,380 --> 00:16:21,990
He still acts like you belong to him,
calling you, "my wife, Han Young Ja."

296
00:16:22,950 --> 00:16:24,020
It's pathetic, isn't it?

297
00:16:24,690 --> 00:16:26,960
Especially seeing him
come crawling to CEO Chae.

298
00:16:32,830 --> 00:16:36,870
That jerk. How dare he waltz in here
and talk that way?

299
00:16:37,900 --> 00:16:40,470
What do you mean, "in here"?
This is Han Young Ja's house.

300
00:16:40,970 --> 00:16:41,970
What?

301
00:16:42,640 --> 00:16:43,670
Unbelievable.

302
00:16:45,280 --> 00:16:48,410
Maybe it's because Manager Lee is single.

303
00:16:48,410 --> 00:16:50,110
He doesn't have that old-man smell.

304
00:16:52,350 --> 00:16:54,080
I think he even wears cologne.

305
00:16:54,490 --> 00:16:55,750
He's surprisingly charming, you know?

306
00:16:55,990 --> 00:16:59,590
Are you saying I have an old-man smell?

307
00:17:01,830 --> 00:17:02,930
You're just now figuring that out?

308
00:17:04,460 --> 00:17:06,960
Chae Hwa Young must have
terrible taste in men.

309
00:17:07,330 --> 00:17:10,700
She had Manager Lee right there,
but somehow...

310
00:17:11,070 --> 00:17:13,200
she ended up choosing a man like you?

311
00:17:15,110 --> 00:17:16,110
Then again,

312
00:17:16,510 --> 00:17:18,210
I guess I could be saying
the same thing about myself.

313
00:17:18,280 --> 00:17:20,210
What?
Han Young Ja, have you said your piece?

314
00:17:21,110 --> 00:17:22,880
I guess I was the one with terrible taste.

315
00:17:33,390 --> 00:17:34,390
Darn it.

316
00:17:37,230 --> 00:17:39,260
Great. It's all soggy.

317
00:17:45,570 --> 00:17:48,770
Professor Kang, I'm really busy right now.
Can we talk later?

318
00:17:49,010 --> 00:17:52,840
Why haven't you fired Manager Lee yet?

319
00:17:52,910 --> 00:17:55,680
Hwa Young, you don't actually like
that punk, do you?

320
00:17:56,250 --> 00:17:59,280
Professor Kang,
what kind of nonsense is that?

321
00:18:00,280 --> 00:18:02,550
- Hyuk is just...
- You call him Hyuk?

322
00:18:02,550 --> 00:18:03,620
Hyuk?

323
00:18:03,690 --> 00:18:05,690
You're on a first-name basis with him?

324
00:18:06,120 --> 00:18:09,630
You've been calling me Professor Kang
and staying distant.

325
00:18:09,890 --> 00:18:13,100
Goodness.
Why are you being like this, Nam Bong?

326
00:18:13,460 --> 00:18:15,330
I'm stuck working for Oh Jang Mi...

327
00:18:15,670 --> 00:18:17,800
and taking all her abuse
as an entry-level employee now.

328
00:18:18,140 --> 00:18:20,140
How can you give me a hard time too?

329
00:18:20,670 --> 00:18:22,210
I'm going through a lot right now.

330
00:18:23,510 --> 00:18:25,180
You're finally calling me
by my name again.

331
00:18:25,880 --> 00:18:29,150
For you, Nam Bong,
I can say it 100, even 1,000 times.

332
00:18:29,880 --> 00:18:32,420
So please, Nam Bong,
just try to understand my situation.

333
00:18:33,780 --> 00:18:36,050
Okay, I'm sorry for bothering you
while you're busy.

334
00:18:36,050 --> 00:18:37,890
Call me later when you are free.

335
00:18:38,320 --> 00:18:39,360
Okay.

336
00:18:41,020 --> 00:18:42,030
Unbelievable.

337
00:18:42,230 --> 00:18:45,530
This is no time for me to be
playing silly romantic games.

338
00:18:48,570 --> 00:18:50,600
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

339
00:18:52,140 --> 00:18:53,240
Then it's possible...

340
00:18:53,840 --> 00:18:57,410
that you and my mom might have met before.

341
00:18:58,940 --> 00:19:02,880
To think the pregnant woman I met
at the villa was Jang Mi's mother...

342
00:19:04,720 --> 00:19:06,450
Then the baby she was carrying...

343
00:19:07,120 --> 00:19:08,990
must have been Jang Mi and Seo Rin.

344
00:19:12,320 --> 00:19:13,660
What a crazy coincidence.

345
00:19:14,860 --> 00:19:16,130
Jang Mi and I...

346
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:19,200
must be destined to be together.

347
00:19:22,030 --> 00:19:23,800
If I go to Suk Hee's Side Dish Shop,

348
00:19:24,430 --> 00:19:26,170
will I be able to see her mom there?

349
00:19:31,340 --> 00:19:33,080
It was a split heart necklace.

350
00:19:33,510 --> 00:19:36,780
My brother-in-law had one half,
and my sister had the other.

351
00:19:36,980 --> 00:19:39,950
So they shared an unmistakable
token of their love.

352
00:19:40,250 --> 00:19:44,760
That wretched housekeeper
apparently put it around Eun Hye's neck.

353
00:19:47,160 --> 00:19:48,260
That necklace...

354
00:19:48,990 --> 00:19:50,530
That necklace is the problem.

355
00:19:51,330 --> 00:19:53,060
I have to get my hands on it
and destroy it.

356
00:19:56,070 --> 00:19:58,800
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

357
00:20:03,770 --> 00:20:04,810
Welcome.

358
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:06,510
The side dishes are delicious.

359
00:20:06,510 --> 00:20:08,050
I can't believe...

360
00:20:08,450 --> 00:20:10,050
that kind woman I met at the villa...

361
00:20:10,780 --> 00:20:12,080
is really Jang Mi's mother.

362
00:20:12,950 --> 00:20:16,450
It's delicious.
Suk Hee's cooking is delicious.

363
00:20:19,820 --> 00:20:22,260
I'll have this one and this one, please.

364
00:20:25,330 --> 00:20:26,330
Just a moment.

365
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:34,270
Jun Ho.

366
00:20:36,170 --> 00:20:37,510
What are you doing here?

367
00:20:38,740 --> 00:20:42,850
- It's the thief! The thief is back!
- What are you doing here?

368
00:20:43,150 --> 00:20:46,420
Chae Hwa Young stole that hairpin
from my house.

369
00:20:48,820 --> 00:20:50,950
What are you plotting this time?

370
00:20:51,250 --> 00:20:53,090
What are you planning to do
to Jang Mi's mother?

371
00:20:53,390 --> 00:20:54,890
Plotting? What are you talking about?

372
00:20:57,390 --> 00:20:59,560
I need to get my hands on
that necklace right now.

373
00:21:00,030 --> 00:21:01,930
Why did Jun Ho have to be here
of all times?

374
00:21:02,700 --> 00:21:04,030
Then why did you come here?

375
00:21:07,870 --> 00:21:09,370
Come on. Let's go.

376
00:21:09,640 --> 00:21:11,940
Jun Ho, I was just getting
some side dishes...

377
00:21:12,810 --> 00:21:13,810
Jun Ho!

378
00:21:14,210 --> 00:21:15,280
The thief came back.

379
00:21:16,010 --> 00:21:19,220
I need to get the salt out again. Thief.

380
00:21:26,020 --> 00:21:27,320
What have you done?

381
00:21:27,720 --> 00:21:29,630
And why did you go to
Jang Mi's mother's shop?

382
00:21:29,960 --> 00:21:31,090
How did you find out already?

383
00:21:31,760 --> 00:21:32,830
News travels fast.

384
00:21:33,330 --> 00:21:36,430
Turns out my history with Jang Mi
goes way further back than yours.

385
00:21:37,200 --> 00:21:38,800
A very deep and fateful one, at that.

386
00:21:38,870 --> 00:21:41,140
You mean when you met
her mother at the villa?

387
00:21:41,610 --> 00:21:43,840
I already heard. So what?

388
00:21:43,910 --> 00:21:46,040
That's the one thing you always hold
over my head, isn't it?

389
00:21:47,080 --> 00:21:49,110
That you fell for Jang Mi first.

390
00:21:50,080 --> 00:21:51,110
Guess what?

391
00:21:51,780 --> 00:21:53,020
You've got the order wrong.

392
00:21:53,820 --> 00:21:55,690
I knew Jang Mi first.

393
00:21:55,750 --> 00:21:58,020
That's the most ridiculous,
twisted logic I've ever heard.

394
00:21:58,620 --> 00:22:01,460
Stop obsessing over some flimsy connection
and calling it destiny.

395
00:22:01,530 --> 00:22:02,530
You know it's true.

396
00:22:03,430 --> 00:22:06,100
I was the one who made her twenties
shine the brightest,

397
00:22:06,800 --> 00:22:10,100
and the only person she could lean on
was me, Kang Jun Ho.

398
00:22:10,170 --> 00:22:11,540
No, you get this straight.

399
00:22:12,470 --> 00:22:14,540
Whatever feelings Jang Mi had
for you back then...

400
00:22:14,870 --> 00:22:17,010
were just blind admiration, not love.

401
00:22:17,770 --> 00:22:22,110
And what's most important is that now,
Jang Mi doesn't respect you one bit.

402
00:22:22,410 --> 00:22:24,920
- In fact, she despises you.
- And how would you prove that?

403
00:22:25,850 --> 00:22:27,950
Did you crawl inside her mind?

404
00:22:29,150 --> 00:22:30,920
What makes you so sure?

405
00:22:31,790 --> 00:22:35,030
Because love isn't based
on some petty calculation.

406
00:22:35,630 --> 00:22:37,330
It's built on unwavering trust.

407
00:22:38,260 --> 00:22:40,900
I know Jang Mi, and she knows me.

408
00:22:41,160 --> 00:22:42,170
We'll see about that.

409
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:44,470
You can look forward to it, Kang Baek Ho.

410
00:22:45,100 --> 00:22:48,940
I'm going to prove just how miserably
that arrogant, flimsy faith of yours...

411
00:22:50,370 --> 00:22:52,340
is about to be shattered.

412
00:22:55,080 --> 00:22:56,310
I'm warning you.

413
00:22:57,610 --> 00:22:59,620
If you use another pathetic excuse
to mess with my woman,

414
00:23:00,750 --> 00:23:02,420
I swear I'll kill you
with my own two hands.

415
00:23:04,590 --> 00:23:05,790
And here's a warning for you.

416
00:23:06,820 --> 00:23:08,430
Stay away from Oh Jang Mi.

417
00:23:09,730 --> 00:23:12,100
Because I can make her much happier
than someone like you ever could.

418
00:23:23,410 --> 00:23:24,410
I have something for you.

419
00:23:24,880 --> 00:23:25,910
What is it?

420
00:23:26,780 --> 00:23:27,780
This.

421
00:23:29,880 --> 00:23:31,310
Where did you find this?

422
00:23:31,380 --> 00:23:34,350
I found it under Seo Rin's bed
while I was cleaning.

423
00:23:34,720 --> 00:23:36,750
I wonder how it ended up
all the way there.

424
00:23:37,290 --> 00:23:39,960
Could you put it back on
Seo Rin's lipstick stand for me?

425
00:23:41,090 --> 00:23:42,790
Okay, I will.

426
00:23:55,740 --> 00:23:57,310
Seo Rin, come have some fruit.

427
00:23:58,510 --> 00:24:00,080
You and your daughter can have it.

428
00:24:00,840 --> 00:24:04,050
Anyway, you really haven't
seen my lipstick?

429
00:24:05,620 --> 00:24:09,720
Why do you keep accusing me
when you're the one who lost it?

430
00:24:10,090 --> 00:24:11,660
That lipstick?

431
00:24:12,020 --> 00:24:16,160
- The one with that unique color.
- What? So you had it?

432
00:24:16,230 --> 00:24:20,560
No, I found it under your bed
and put it in my apron pocket.

433
00:24:20,630 --> 00:24:23,030
So? Did you look inside it?

434
00:24:23,170 --> 00:24:26,340
Look inside? Of course not.
Why would I go through your things?

435
00:24:26,800 --> 00:24:29,540
Jang Mi was just here,
so I gave it to her to put in your room.

436
00:24:29,610 --> 00:24:32,340
Why would you give it to Oh Jang Mi?
Are you crazy?

437
00:24:43,090 --> 00:24:44,090
My lipstick.

438
00:24:52,660 --> 00:24:54,430
You're back.

439
00:24:55,130 --> 00:24:57,770
What are you doing here again?
I told you I didn't want to see you.

440
00:24:57,870 --> 00:25:00,840
You may not, but I missed you, so I came.
What about it?

441
00:25:00,940 --> 00:25:02,910
Get out. I need to get some rest.

442
00:25:03,640 --> 00:25:07,210
What? Where's the lipstick
I put back earlier?

443
00:25:07,810 --> 00:25:10,410
Did you look inside my lipstick?

444
00:25:10,510 --> 00:25:12,850
No, I just put it back on the stand.

445
00:25:13,550 --> 00:25:14,920
So she really didn't look?

446
00:25:15,590 --> 00:25:16,790
If she had looked,

447
00:25:17,050 --> 00:25:19,590
she would have asked
if it was the USB with the evidence.

448
00:25:20,320 --> 00:25:21,320
Does she really not know?

449
00:25:21,730 --> 00:25:23,160
Fine, get your rest.

450
00:25:25,760 --> 00:25:26,760
Hey, Tae Pyung.

451
00:25:32,040 --> 00:25:34,700
It's a relief that I think Oh Jang Mi
didn't look inside.

452
00:25:35,270 --> 00:25:37,010
It'll just be a huge headache for me
if she finds out.

453
00:25:38,170 --> 00:25:40,910
Anyway, what am I going to do
with that thing?

454
00:25:51,120 --> 00:25:53,790
(Genos Gene Examination Center,
Genetic Analysis Report)

455
00:25:59,730 --> 00:26:02,200
All right.
Especially with her father dead,

456
00:26:02,470 --> 00:26:04,800
we need to make her so busy
just putting food on the table...

457
00:26:05,340 --> 00:26:07,370
that she can't think about anything else.

458
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:10,640
- What about the police?
- The investigation's been closed.

459
00:26:10,770 --> 00:26:12,010
So the chief pulled some strings.

460
00:26:14,410 --> 00:26:15,810
All right, that's settled then.

461
00:26:16,310 --> 00:26:18,210
Now we just have to keep a close eye
on Seo Rin.

462
00:26:20,880 --> 00:26:23,120
So Seo Rin was the one who recorded this.

463
00:26:23,820 --> 00:26:27,590
Yes, I made a copy of
what was on the lipstick USB.

464
00:26:28,260 --> 00:26:31,060
Do you think this is enough
to corner Chae Hwa Young?

465
00:26:31,360 --> 00:26:33,630
This time,
we can't let her get away with it.

466
00:26:33,930 --> 00:26:37,630
Yes, and if Grandfather finds
his biological daughter,

467
00:26:37,930 --> 00:26:40,440
he probably won't cover for
Chae Hwa Young this time.

468
00:26:41,100 --> 00:26:43,710
Did you look into that imposter
Park Young Mi's background?

469
00:26:43,910 --> 00:26:47,240
Yes, sir. It's true she was at
the Chuncheon Orphanage.

470
00:26:47,540 --> 00:26:50,610
However, most of the records were lost
in a fire at the time,

471
00:26:50,810 --> 00:26:52,680
and the director has since passed away.

472
00:26:54,350 --> 00:26:57,690
But by questioning the regulars
at her restaurant,

473
00:26:58,050 --> 00:26:59,820
we've secured a crucial piece
of testimony.

474
00:27:00,160 --> 00:27:01,220
Testimony?

475
00:27:01,520 --> 00:27:03,390
Apparently, she was bragging
while drinking one night.

476
00:27:04,790 --> 00:27:07,330
She said that back at the orphanage,
while they weren't very close,

477
00:27:07,660 --> 00:27:09,330
there was another girl about her age.

478
00:27:09,900 --> 00:27:12,400
- Really?
- Yes. And the necklace she wore...

479
00:27:12,840 --> 00:27:14,740
made it obvious
she came from a wealthy family.

480
00:27:15,470 --> 00:27:18,410
So she hoped to get a small reward
if the girl's parents ever showed up,

481
00:27:18,840 --> 00:27:20,780
and she apparently stuck to her
like a leech.

482
00:27:21,080 --> 00:27:24,510
- So, that girl...
- Yes, that's correct.

483
00:27:24,810 --> 00:27:26,520
And then what?

484
00:27:26,720 --> 00:27:29,790
The girl was a good student
and went on to high school,

485
00:27:30,720 --> 00:27:35,460
but the impostor quit middle school,
and they apparently lost touch after that.

486
00:27:38,290 --> 00:27:41,200
And there's one more crucial fact.

487
00:27:43,500 --> 00:27:45,770
The name Park Young Mi
that the impostor uses...

488
00:27:46,500 --> 00:27:48,000
isn't actually her real name.

489
00:27:48,940 --> 00:27:53,080
It was the name of the girl
with the necklace at the orphanage.

490
00:27:54,210 --> 00:27:55,210
What?

491
00:27:55,280 --> 00:27:58,680
When she registered for a resident ID,
she took the name Park Young Mi.

492
00:27:59,580 --> 00:28:00,620
Then that means...

493
00:28:01,580 --> 00:28:04,450
there's another Park Young Mi.

494
00:28:05,360 --> 00:28:06,360
Yes, sir.

495
00:28:07,390 --> 00:28:11,390
That other girl,
the one named Park Young Mi...

496
00:28:12,960 --> 00:28:14,730
could be my Eun Hye.

497
00:28:15,800 --> 00:28:17,530
Find her now!

498
00:28:17,970 --> 00:28:21,170
Scour the country for every Park Young Mi
if you have to.

499
00:28:21,640 --> 00:28:23,940
You must find my daughter, Eun Hye!

500
00:28:48,930 --> 00:28:50,430
(The First Man)

501
00:28:50,500 --> 00:28:52,200
Chae Hwa Young, this is Han Young Ja.

502
00:28:52,300 --> 00:28:54,800
What were you doing with Han Young Ja
for her to answer your phone?

503
00:28:54,940 --> 00:28:56,110
That's my personal life.

504
00:28:56,370 --> 00:28:58,270
Hey, Kang Hyuk.
Are you really going to do this to me?

505
00:28:58,610 --> 00:29:01,310
I'm going to take that
monster Chae Hwa Young down this time.

506
00:29:01,540 --> 00:29:04,380
That's odd.
Why were they running away like that?

507
00:29:04,780 --> 00:29:07,750
Now, there's no way Jung Suk Hee
can become Chairman Ma's daughter now.

508
00:29:08,280 --> 00:29:11,960
Isn't this the necklace
Grandfather gave to his lost daughter?

509
00:29:12,690 --> 00:29:15,290
Mom, are you Grandfather's daughter?

510
